comment: He in all likelihood had a different lawyer in England since their justice system is quite different from ours and I doubt there are many of any lawyers licensed to practice in both England and the US. Also in the US you have to be licensed to practice in particular states whereas in England it's at a national level. There's also no single "lawyer" in England. They have what are called solicitors and barristers. Solicitors interact with the client and the barrister represents them in court. It's actually pretty confusing for anyone used to our court system.
